.SH NAME
vapi-listen - Forward webhook events to your local server


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBvapi listen [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Start a webhook listener that forwards Vapi webhook events to your local development server.

.PP
This is perfect for testing webhooks during development without needing ngrok or other tunneling tools.
The CLI will create a secure tunnel and forward all webhook events to your specified local endpoint.

.PP
Examples:
  vapi listen --forward-to localhost:3000/webhook
  vapi listen --forward-to http://localhost:8080/api/webhooks --port 4242
  vapi listen --forward-to localhost:3000/webhook --skip-verify


.SH OPTIONS
\fB--forward-to\fP=""
	Local endpoint to forward webhooks to (e.g., localhost:3000/webhook)

.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for listen

.PP
\fB--port\fP=4242
	Port to listen on for incoming webhooks

.PP
\fB--skip-verify\fP[=false]
	Skip TLS certificate verification when forwarding


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--api-key\fP=""
	Vapi API key

.PP
\fB--config\fP=""
	config file (default is ./.vapi-cli.yaml or $HOME/.vapi-cli.yaml)


